,Recommended,216110,74557,"Posted: 24 November, 2012",all,Toxic League,"This is actually a decent top view action shooter. The gameplay is very similar to Foreign Legion: Buckets of Blood, but I found Tiny Troopers to be much more fun. During the short 3 chapter campaign, you accumulate points to spend on non-permanent upgrades including a specialist soldier. During the missions, you pickup usable items like grenades, RPGs, and air strikes. Then you collect medals to spend on permanent recruitment upgrades. Your characters gain experience as long as you keep them alive; if they die, you get new fresh troops. The game does lack controller support which would make the gameplay even better, but you can't go wrong for $2. Did I mention the endless zombie survival mode?"
