,Not Recommended,216110,28289135,"Posted: 10 December, 2016",all,ZenosyX,"Pretty goofy and fairly relaxing game, definitely something I can see casual gamers enjoy.There is a bit of a puzzle aspect to it in some degree while completing missions through obtaining certain tools required and/or decide what to bring for the mission. But overall it has for me mostly been either a test of patience to take a mission in my own pace and attempt to beat it without any upgrades for more challenge while making sure every soldier stay alive, or grinding up some cash to buy all upgrades and try to stomp the missions head on.Once you figure out a few mechanics it's mostly played on ""autopilot"" (meaning: doesn't require much thinking at all) besides the occasional times you need certain tools and take certain routes to make it a bit easier for yourself. But even those can most of the time be dealt with straight on if you want to and understand the game mechanics well enough to use them for your advantage. It is far from a difficult game, and I only tried it on the hardest difficulty when trying to get a feel of what the game was like.In my personal opinion, this game could have been more optimized and they could have made several mechanics much smoother, but overall it is somehow pretty charming with its goofy graphics, sounds and silly comments here and there. It's not really a bad game, it just simply isn't made for me.I really don't think this is a game people should buy unless it is on sale or if they notice that the genre suit them too good to pass up on it. However, if you just want a relaxing way to kill time and it's on a big sale then who knows?On a sidenote: they should really fix the duplication glitch where you are able to bring two specialists to a mission. I found it by accident and realized it had a 100% chance to occur during certain circumstances. It really takes the fun out of the game when it happens... and the fact that you are able to do it really easy intentionally can probably make some people unable to avoid abusing it, which may ruin their experience with it."
