76561198047455459,Recommended,216110,15144370,"Posted: 31 March, 2015",all,Spectre,"Though not a perfect game by any means it's hard to really chastise it when the game only costs 0.99.  My verdict is this: If you're looking for an easy to learn, basic mechanic top down shooter then you will definitely enjoy this game but if you go into it looking for a well thought out deep tactical experience, one might find themselves a little disappointed. The mechanics are very simple, you lead a squad (every member of your squad automatically follows the unit you control so no worries about micro or positioning) and complete objectives based on each level (this is typically ""kill all enemy units"", or escort ""unit A to point B"" typ stuff) while along the way there are hidden items that will allow you to purchase temporary upgrades and equiptment for your men at the end of each level. However you also have to ability to call in med kits, grenades, and other equiptment at any point during a mission so as long as you don't get completely surrounded you can almost always keep your men alive.The game's squad tries to take on an Xcom style approach where as a soldier completes missions and survives he will get promoted with gives him a series of buffs and enhancements. Similarly however if a soldier dies he is gone for good and is replaced with a lower ranking soldier. This part can be very frustrating since there is no save option during the campaign so if one your men dies he's gone no matter what. To make up for this though the player can replay individual missions of the campaign and receive a seperate squad of soldiers than his main campaign squad.The combat is very basic. Youre squad follows you in a line, you Point and click to shoot, no cover, no ammo, no changing positions. Certain items like armor and grenades can be purchased between missions to add some variables into how the combat will play out.The graphics are pretty well done even though i'm almost convinced it uses the same engine as Diablo or Torchlight. The sound effects and voice acting are all intentionally cheesy and exagerated which suits the light heartedness of the game very well. All in all the asking price is pretty fair and if you're into top down point and click shooters or MOBA style combat then you will definitely get some enjoyment out of this game."
